This library adapts and extends the Android WebAuthn Authenticator Library provided
by Duo Labs (https://github.com/duo-labs/android-webauthn-authenticator)

The functionality has been improved and extended to:
- directly work with an emulated Bluetooth HID device transport layer
- provide easy message handling, framing and transport layer support mechanisms
- add mandatory strong biometric user verification has been added
- add client PIN support to the authenticator together with the client PIN
crypto locker guarded by the Android KeyStore and strong authentication
- add extension definitions as per CTAP2 spec (e.g. txAuthSimple, hmac-secret)
- add extended credentials management guarded by strong authentication 
- add proper U2F support for legacy websites (U2F primitive handling + attestations)
- enhance WebAuthn support via BasicAttestations both in self-signed and full forms
- fix previous bugs and todos 

NOTE: Neither the original Copyright holder nor the contributors to the reference
project endorse this work.

